news.title: Gmada norms on PGs openly violated in Mohali
news.para: The PG policy constituted by Gmada was not implemented in the past five years. According to Gmada records, there are over 600 PGs in Mohali but only 83 are registered with the authority.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body plans tax camps to meet Rs 50 crore target till March 2023
news.para: Earlier this year, the civic body organised weekly tax camps across several wards, mostly in the Rajarhat-Gopalpur area from where the authorities collected an average of about Rs 4.5 lakh as property tax and mutation fee from each camp.

news.title: Special drive in January 2023 to provide land to homeless: Madhya Pradesh CM
news.para: ​Chouhan said that those who do not have a plot of land to live in the village, will be provided free lease for residential house on the basis of applications received in the campaign being started from January 4, 2023.

news.title: Material seized from 347 buildings that ignored 'stop-work' notices in Chennai
news.para: Among the 347 buildings where the civic body's officials seized construction material, the highest number, 69, was in Anna Nagar, followed by 44 in Tondiarpet, 39 in Perungudi and 38 in Madhavaram.

news.title: Can't deny payout due to Covid, revocation of OC: Goa RERA
news.para: Taking note of lengthy delays in completion of the project, the Goa Rera directed Venkatesh Prabhu Moni to pay Rs 4 crore to those who had purchased flats and shops in Prabhu Chambers.

news.title: Just one application cleared in a month after architects allowed to issue OC in Gurugram
news.para: It appears that architects aren’t clear about the process or they don’t want to be part of the process due to fears that any errors or violations of building code could get them blacklisted, DTCP officials said on Sunday.

news.title: Ghaziabad: 4,700 flats yet to be sold, UP housing board slashes rates by 20%
news.para: “We decided to slash the rates of dwelling units under all the UP Housing Board housing schemes by 20% to make the rates compatible with market rates and woo homebuyers,” said Sunil Kumar Sharma, property in charge of the state housing board.

news.title: Registries pending, homebuyers in Greater Noida west protest
news.para: Homebuyers from societies like Supertech UpCountry, Supertech Eco Village 1, 2 and 3, Apex Golf Avenue, Amaatra Homes, Casa Greens 1, Ajnara Homes, JM Florence, Earthcon Sanskriti, Gaur City 1 and 2, etc., joined the protest.

news.title: Private equity investment in real estate down 17% to $5.13 billion
news.para: In office assets, PE investment dipped 19 per cent to USD 2,331 million this year from USD 2,882 million in 2021. PE inflows were down 50 per cent in the housing segment to USD 594 million in 2022 from USD 1,187 million last year.

news.title: Purbanchal Cement lines up Rs 200 crore for expansion
news.para: "We are evaluating between brownfield expansion and acquisition preferably with mine rights in the northern part of Assam," Purbanchal Cement MD Vedant Agarwal said.

news.title: Mumbai: Housing society ordered to pay flat owner Rs 1.2 lakh over failure to fix leakage
news.para: The complainant, Lourdes Dias, alleged that the problem arose due to the unauthorised changes made by the owners of four flats in the adjacent wing. The commission said that the society should have taken stringent measures against those flat owners.

news.title: Pune: PMRDA spots 972 illegal structures, pulls down 85
news.para: Seven FIRs have been lodged in connection with illegal plotting in the Pune Metropolitan Region (PMR) and 15 more would be registered next week, a senior Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority (PMRDA) official said.

news.title: Government to conduct drone survey in Mangaluru to ascertain details of all properties
news.para: While the Mangaluru Smart City Limited (MSCL) has already conducted a drone survey in 20 wards of the city corporation, the government has plans to conduct a drone survey through an agency, in the remaining 40 wards.

news.title: Zirakpur to undergo digital survey to assess buildings, sewerage system
news.para: Municipal council president Udayveer Singh Dhillon said in view of the demand to upgrade and lay new sewerage and storm water drainage system in the town, the department water supply and sewerage board Punjab was contacted.

news.title: Apartment terrace common for residents: Chennai court
news.para: The issue pertains to a suit moved by Brindavan Apartment Owners Welfare Association in Kilpauk against Kences Constructions Pvt Ltd, the promoter of the apartment.
